  "prompt": "Where should I register my domain name in Singapore?",
  "response": "In Singapore, you can register your domain name through various accredited registrars authorized by the Singapore Network Information Centre (SGNIC). Some popular options include:\n\n1. **SGNIC Direct Registration**: You can register directly through SGNIC, the official registry for .sg domains.\n\n2. **Web Hosting Companies**: Many web hosting companies also offer domain registration services. Some popular ones in Singapore include:\n   - **Vodien**\n   - **Exabytes**\n   - **Cybersite**\n   - **APC Hosting**\n\n3. **International Domain Registrars**: International registrars like GoDaddy, Namecheap, and Google Domains also offer .sg domain registration.\n\nWhen choosing a registrar, consider factors like pricing, customer service, additional features (like email hosting or additional security features), and ease of use. Ensure that the registrar is accredited by SGNIC to register .sg domains.",
